'''''Mons''''' or '''''Montes''''' are [[Latin]] words used by [[planetary geology|planetary geologists ]] (reference the entire list [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planetary_nomenclature#Descriptor_Terms_.28Feature_Types.29 here]) to refer to [[mountains]] or [[extinct volcano]]es on [[planet]]s and [[natural satellite|moon]]s.  Examples of both uses are [[Maxwell Montes]] ([[Venus]]) and [[Olympus Mons]] ([[Mars]]).

